<br>
I guess I was wrong.<br>
<br>
The crew of 8 I managed to assemble is now homeless. In part, we were hoping to remain together under the banner of a new guild. A few things about us:<br>
<br>
1) We are mostly in the teens and twenties. I think I am the only exception, being at 7 right now.<br>
<br>
2) Of the members I know are interested in going over to a guild together, we have 1 Wood Elves, 1 Froglock, 1 High Elf, 1 Gnome, and 2 Half Elves. Our human Paladin I am not sure about, and my own charector, an Iksar Shaman of neutral persuasion, is low enough that I would not miss re-rolling him too terribly.<br>
<br>
3) The Academy was a roleplaying guild, so we would be looking for a roleplaying guild as well. With Followers of Tunare and the Marr's in our ranks we are generally more aimed towards the Good side of things.<br>
<br>
If need be, we may be willnig to split up I suppose. Still, togehter we are a loyal band, and it's always sad to break up a good act. <p>----------------<br>
