<br>
I am sorry to see that your guild didn't work out. I was watching from afar on these boards as you were trying to put an idea into action, and I thought your enthusiasm was admirable. I am not sure it is for you, but my guild, The Emerald Family, is an Elf-only Family that has a lot of fun roleplaying, with about 60 players ranging in level from 5 to 56. Now I know you mentioned that you wanted to stay together with your non-Elven friends, which would be pretty much impossible in the Family. That being said, we are in a burgeoning alliance of good-aligned roleplaying guilds, the Gateway Alliance, which shares a chat channel and a new messageboard, so I would imagine there is a possibility of you and your friends staying close. <br>
<br>
